<h1 class="doc-page-title">API documentation</h1>
<p class="doc-page-lead">COMPASS provides a RESTful API for programmatic access to RAID data, metrics, and reporting.</p>

<h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

        <div class="alert alert-info">
            <p class="mb-0">The COMPASS API is currently available for internal use. External API access requires authorisation from the COMPASS team.</p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Base URL</h3>
        <div class="api-code-block">
            <pre>Production:  https://compass.education.gov.uk/api
Test:        https://compass-test.education.gov.uk/api
Development: http://localhost:5500/api</pre>
        </div>

        <h3 class="h5 mt-4">API version</h3>
        <p>Current API version: <code>v1</code></p>
        <p>The API version is included in the endpoint path: <code>/api/v1/{resource}</code></p>

        <hr class="my-4">

        <h2 id="authentication">Authentication</h2>
        
        <h3 class="h5 mt-4">API token authentication</h3>
        <p>The COMPASS API uses bearer token authentication. API tokens can be generated and managed through the admin interface.</p>

        <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Creating an API token:</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to <strong>Settings → API tokens</strong> in the admin interface</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Create token</strong></li>
            <li>Provide a descriptive name (e.g. "PowerBI-Integration", "SAS-ReadOnly")</li>
            <li>Optionally set an expiry date</li>
            <li>Configure granular permissions for each resource</li>
            <li>Copy the generated token (you won't be able to see it again)</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="alert alert-info mt-3">
            <p class="mb-0">Only administrators can create and manage API tokens.</p>
        </div>

        <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Using your API token:</h4>
        <p>Include the API token in the Authorization header of your requests:</p>
        <div class="api-code-block">
            <pre>Authorization: Bearer cps_your_token_here</pre>
        </div>

        <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Example request:</h4>
        <div class="api-code-block">
            <pre>curl -H "Authorization: Bearer cps_your_token_here" \
     https://compass.education.gov.uk/api/v1/risks</pre>
        </div>

        <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Token management:</h4>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Permissions:</strong> Each token has granular permissions (read, create, update, delete) for each resource</li>
            <li><strong>Status:</strong> Tokens can be enabled/disabled without deleting them</li>
            <li><strong>Expiry:</strong> Tokens can be set to expire automatically</li>
            <li><strong>Logging:</strong> All API requests and responses are logged for audit purposes</li>
            <li><strong>Last used:</strong> Track when each token was last used</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Permission scopes</h4>
        <p>Scopes determine which controllers a token can reach. Each scope carries four verbs (<code>read</code>, <code>create</code>, <code>update</code>, <code>delete</code>):</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Risks:</strong> Access to <code>/api/v1/risks</code> for register operations.</li>
            <li><strong>Actions:</strong> Access to <code>/api/v1/actions</code> for mitigation tracking.</li>
            <li><strong>Issues</strong> and <strong>Milestones:</strong> Equivalent scopes to manage other RAID artefacts.</li>
            <li><strong>Administration:</strong> Separate scopes exist for lookup management and template configuration in the admin namespace.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="small text-muted">Assign the narrowest set of scopes needed for each integration. Tokens created for reporting purposes typically require read-only access to Risks and Actions.</p>

        <div class="alert alert-warning mt-3">
            <p class="mb-0">Keep your API tokens secure. Never commit them to version control or share them publicly.</p>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-4">

        <h2 id="endpoints">API endpoints</h2>

        <!-- Health Check Endpoint -->
        <div class="api-endpoint">
            <div class="api-endpoint-header">
                <span class="api-method api-method-get">GET</span>
                <span class="api-path">/api/health</span>
                <span class="ml-auto"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
            </div>
            <div class="api-endpoint-body">
                <p>Verify API availability and health status.</p>
                
                <ul class="nav nav-tabs api-section-tabs" role="tablist">
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a class="nav-link active" data-toggle="tab" href="#health-response">Response</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="health-response">
                        <h5 class="mt-3"><span class="api-response-code api-response-200">200 OK</span></h5>
                        <div class="api-code-block">
                            <pre>{
  "status": "healthy",
  "timestamp": "2025-10-19T10:30:00Z"
}</pre>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Get All Risks Endpoint -->
        <div class="api-endpoint">
            <div class="api-endpoint-header">
                <span class="api-method api-method-get">GET</span>
                <span class="api-path">/api/v1/risks</span>
                <span class="ml-auto"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
            </div>
            <div class="api-endpoint-body">
                <p>Retrieve a list of all risks with optional filtering.</p>
                
                <ul class="nav nav-tabs api-section-tabs" role="tablist">
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a class="nav-link active" data-toggle="tab" href="#risks-get-params">Parameters</a>
                    </li>
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a class="nav-link" data-toggle="tab" href="#risks-get-response">Response</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="risks-get-params">
                        <h5 class="mt-3">Query parameters</h5>
                        <table class="api-param-table">
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Parameter</th>
                                    <th>Type</th>
                                    <th>Description</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-name">fipsId</span></td>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-type">string</span></td>
                                    <td>Filter by FIPS product ID</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-name">status</span></td>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-type">string</span></td>
                                    <td>Filter by status (new, open, treating, monitoring, closed)</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-name">minScore</span></td>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-type">integer</span></td>
                                    <td>Filter by minimum risk score (1-25)</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-name">page</span></td>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-type">integer</span></td>
                                    <td>Page number (default: 1)</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-name">pageSize</span></td>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-type">integer</span></td>
                                    <td>Results per page (default: 50, max: 100)</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="risks-get-response">
                        <h5 class="mt-3"><span class="api-response-code api-response-200">200 OK</span></h5>
                        <div class="api-code-block">
                            <pre>{
  "data": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "title": "Risk title",
      "description": "Risk description",
      "fipsId": "PROD123",
      "impactRating": 4,
      "likelihoodRating": 3,
      "riskScore": 12,
      "status": "open",
      "createdAt": "2025-10-01T09:00:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2025-10-15T14:30:00Z"
    }
  ],
  "pagination": {
    "currentPage": 1,
    "pageSize": 50,
    "totalPages": 5,
    "totalRecords": 223
  }
}</pre>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Create Risk Endpoint -->
        <div class="api-endpoint">
            <div class="api-endpoint-header">
                <span class="api-method api-method-post">POST</span>
                <span class="api-path">/api/v1/risks</span>
                <span class="ml-auto"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
            </div>
            <div class="api-endpoint-body">
                <p>Create a new risk, optionally linking it to risk types and an objective.</p>

                <ul class="nav nav-tabs api-section-tabs" role="tablist">
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a class="nav-link active" data-toggle="tab" href="#risks-post-request">Request</a>
                    </li>
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a class="nav-link" data-toggle="tab" href="#risks-post-response">Response</a>
                    </li>
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a class="nav-link" data-toggle="tab" href="#risks-post-try">Try it</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="risks-post-request">
                        <h5 class="mt-3">JSON payload</h5>
                        <div class="api-code-block">
                            <pre>{
  "title": "Data quality risk",
  "description": "Missing source system feeds for April reporting",
  "fipsId": "PROG-0148",
  "objectiveId": 12,
  "riskTierId": 3,
  "impactRating": 4,
  "likelihoodRating": 3,
  "ownerEmail": "programme.manager@education.gov.uk",
  "status": "open",
  "category": "data",
  "businessArea": "Digital Delivery",
  "proximityDate": "2025-12-01T00:00:00Z",
  "targetDate": "2026-01-15T00:00:00Z",
  "response": "mitigate",
  "riskTypeIds": [2, 7]
}</pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="small text-muted">Provide at least impact and likelihood scores. <code>riskTypeIds</code> accepts an array so you can tag a single risk with multiple themes.</p>

                        <h5 class="mt-4">Field reference</h5>
                        <table class="api-param-table">
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Field</th>
                                    <th>Type</th>
                                    <th>Description</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-name">title</span> <span class="api-param-required">required</span></td>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-type">string</span></td>
                                    <td>Brief descriptive title (max 200 characters).</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-name">description</span></td>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-type">string</span></td>
                                    <td>Detailed risk narrative for context.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-name">fipsId</span></td>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-type">string</span></td>
                                    <td>External identifier that links back to FIPS CMS.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-name">objectiveId</span></td>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-type">integer</span></td>
                                    <td>Strategic objective reference (optional).</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-name">riskTierId</span></td>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-type">integer</span></td>
                                    <td>Governance tier lookup (project, programme, portfolio, etc.).</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-name">impactRating</span> <span class="api-param-required">required</span></td>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-type">integer</span></td>
                                    <td>Impact severity (1–5 inclusive).</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-name">likelihoodRating</span> <span class="api-param-required">required</span></td>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-type">integer</span></td>
                                    <td>Likelihood (1–5 inclusive).</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-name">riskTypeIds</span></td>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-type">array&lt;int&gt;</span></td>
                                    <td>List of risk type identifiers enabling multi-select classification.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-name">status</span></td>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-type">string</span></td>
                                    <td>Workflow status (defaults to <code>new</code> if omitted).</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-name">businessArea</span></td>
                                    <td><span class="api-param-type">string</span></td>
                                    <td>Business area label for reporting.</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>

                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="risks-post-response">
                        <h5 class="mt-3"><span class="api-response-code api-response-201">201 Created</span></h5>
                        <div class="api-code-block">
                            <pre>{
  "id": 87,
  "title": "Data quality risk",
  "status": "open",
  "riskScore": 12,
  "createdAt": "2025-11-09T11:05:04Z"
}</pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="small text-muted">Use the <code>Location</code> header or the returned <code>id</code> to fetch the full record.</p>

                        <h5 class="mt-4"><span class="api-response-code api-response-400">400 Bad Request</span></h5>
                        <div class="api-code-block">
                            <pre>{
  "error": {
    "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
    "message": "Invalid request data",
    "details": [
      "ImpactRating must be between 1 and 5",
      "LikelihoodRating must be between 1 and 5"
    ]
  }
}</pre>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="risks-post-try">
                        <h5 class="mt-3">cURL example</h5>
                        <div class="api-code-block">
                            <pre>curl -X POST   -H "Authorization: Bearer cps_your_token_here"   -H "Content-Type: application/json"   https://compass.education.gov.uk/api/v1/risks   -d '{
        "title": "Data quality risk",
        "impactRating": 4,
        "likelihoodRating": 3,
        "riskTypeIds": [2, 7]
      }'</pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="small text-muted">The example truncates optional properties to highlight the minimum viable payload.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

