        <div class="api-endpoint">
            <div class="api-endpoint-header">
                <span class="api-method api-method-put">PUT</span>
                <span class="api-path">/api/v1/risks/{id}</span>
                <span class="ml-auto"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
            </div>
            <div class="api-endpoint-body">
                <p>Update a risk in place. Only the fields supplied are amended; omitted properties keep their previous values.</p>

                <ul class="nav nav-tabs api-section-tabs" role="tablist">
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a class="nav-link active" data-toggle="tab" href="#risks-put-request">Request</a>
                    </li>
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a class="nav-link" data-toggle="tab" href="#risks-put-response">Response</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="risks-put-request">
                        <h5 class="mt-3">Minimum payload</h5>
                        <div class="api-code-block">
                            <pre>{
  "status": "treating",
  "likelihoodRating": 2,
  "response": "mitigate"
}</pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="small text-muted">Recalculation of <code>riskScore</code> happens server-side. Send only the properties that need to change.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="risks-put-response">
                        <h5 class="mt-3"><span class="api-response-code api-response-200">200 OK</span></h5>
                        <div class="api-code-block">
                            <pre>{
  "message": "Risk updated successfully"
}</pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="small text-muted">The API recalculates <code>riskScore</code> on every update using the stored impact and likelihood values.</p>

                        <h5 class="mt-4"><span class="api-response-code api-response-404">404 Not Found</span></h5>
                        <div class="api-code-block">
                            <pre>{
  "error": {
    "code": "NOT_FOUND",
    "message": "Risk with ID 999 not found"
  }
}</pre>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

